export PATH=/usr/local/cuda/bin:$PATH
__global__ in front of a function shows that this function will run on GPU.


GRID:- Collection of all the threads
Block:- Threads in grid are arranged in blocks


GPU contains 5000 to 15000 ALUs.
when one warp waits for the result from the ALU another warp starts executing in GPU as a result latancy(memory bound/airthmatic bound) hiding happens.

shared memory is L1 cache. Sie of shared memory is assigned when kernel code is called.
kernel<<<grid,block,shared_memory_size>>>
Good tutorial on Cuda shared memroy:- https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=upGoZ00MlfI
